41 /// Memory operation flags. Can be ORed together. ----
42 enum class SIMemOp { ----
43 NONE = 0u, ----
44 LOAD = 1u << 0, ----
45 STORE = 1u << 1, ----
46 LLVM_MARK_AS_BITMASK_ENUM(/* LargestFlag = */ STORE) ----
47 }; ----
48 ----
49 /// Position to insert a new instruction relative to an existing ----
50 /// instruction. ----
51 enum class Position { ----
52 BEFORE, ----
53 AFTER ----
54 }; ----
55 ----
56 /// The atomic synchronization scopes supported by the AMDGPU target. ----
57 enum class SIAtomicScope { ----
58 NONE, ----
59 SINGLETHREAD, ----
60 WAVEFRONT, ----
61 WORKGROUP, ----
62 AGENT, ----
63 SYSTEM ----
64 }; ----
65 ----
66 /// The distinct address spaces supported by the AMDGPU target for ----
67 /// atomic memory operation. Can be ORed together. ----
68 enum class SIAtomicAddrSpace { ----
69 NONE = 0u, ----
70 GLOBAL = 1u << 0, ----
71 LDS = 1u << 1, ----
72 SCRATCH = 1u << 2, ----
73 GDS = 1u << 3, ----
74 OTHER = 1u << 4, ----
75 ----
76 /// The address spaces that can be accessed by a FLAT instruction. ----
77 FLAT = GLOBAL | LDS | SCRATCH, ----
78 ----
79 /// The address spaces that support atomic instructions. ----
80 ATOMIC = GLOBAL | LDS | SCRATCH | GDS, ----
81 ----
82 /// All address spaces. ----
83 ALL = GLOBAL | LDS | SCRATCH | GDS | OTHER, ----
84 ----
85 LLVM_MARK_AS_BITMASK_ENUM(/* LargestFlag = */ ALL) ----
86 }; ----

88 class SIMemOpInfo final { ----
89 private: ----
90 ----
91 friend class SIMemOpAccess; ----
92 ----
93 AtomicOrdering Ordering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic; ----
94 AtomicOrdering FailureOrdering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic; ----
95 SIAtomicScope Scope = SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM; ----
96 SIAtomicAddrSpace OrderingAddrSpace = SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE; ----
97 SIAtomicAddrSpace InstrAddrSpace = SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE; ----
98 bool IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering = false; ----
99 bool IsVolatile = false; ----
100 bool IsNonTemporal = false; ----
101 ----
102 SIMemOpInfo(AtomicOrdering Ordering = AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent, 0
103 SIAtomicScope Scope = SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM, ----
104 SIAtomicAddrSpace OrderingAddrSpace = SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC, ----
105 SIAtomicAddrSpace InstrAddrSpace = SIAtomicAddrSpace::ALL, ----
106 bool IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering = true, ----
107 AtomicOrdering FailureOrdering = ----
108 AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent, ----
109 bool IsVolatile = false, ----
110 bool IsNonTemporal = false) ----
111 : Ordering(Ordering), FailureOrdering(FailureOrdering), 0
112 Scope(Scope), OrderingAddrSpace(OrderingAddrSpace), 0
113 InstrAddrSpace(InstrAddrSpace), 0
114 IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering(IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering), 0
115 IsVolatile(IsVolatile), 0
116 IsNonTemporal(IsNonTemporal) { 0
117 ----
118 if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic) { 0
119 assert(Scope == SIAtomicScope::NONE && 0
120 OrderingAddrSpace == SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE && ----
121 !IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering && ----
122 FailureOrdering == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic); ----
123 return; 0
124 } ----
125 ----
126 assert(Scope != SIAtomicScope::NONE && 0
127 (OrderingAddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC) != ----
128 SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE && ----
129 (InstrAddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC) != ----
130 SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE); ----
131 ----
132 // There is also no cross address space ordering if the ordering ----
133 // address space is the same as the instruction address space and ----
134 // only contains a single address space. ----
135 if ((OrderingAddrSpace == InstrAddrSpace) && 0
136 isPowerOf2_32(uint32_t(InstrAddrSpace))) 0
137 this->IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering = false; 0
138 ----
139 // Limit the scope to the maximum supported by the instruction's address ----
140 // spaces. ----
141 if ((InstrAddrSpace & ~SIAtomicAddrSpace::SCRATCH) == 0
142 SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { ----
143 this->Scope = std::min(Scope, SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD); 0
144 } else if ((InstrAddrSpace & 0
145 ~(SIAtomicAddrSpace::SCRATCH | SIAtomicAddrSpace::LDS)) == 0
146 SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { ----
147 this->Scope = std::min(Scope, SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP); 0
148 } else if ((InstrAddrSpace & 0
149 ~(SIAtomicAddrSpace::SCRATCH | SIAtomicAddrSpace::LDS | ----
150 SIAtomicAddrSpace::GDS)) == SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
151 this->Scope = std::min(Scope, SIAtomicScope::AGENT); 0
152 } ----
153 } ----
154 ----
155 public: ----
156 /// \returns Atomic synchronization scope of the machine instruction used to ----
157 /// create this SIMemOpInfo. ----
158 SIAtomicScope getScope() const { 0
159 return Scope; 0
160 } ----
161 ----
162 /// \returns Ordering constraint of the machine instruction used to ----
163 /// create this SIMemOpInfo. ----
164 AtomicOrdering getOrdering() const { 0
165 return Ordering; 0
166 } ----
167 ----
168 /// \returns Failure ordering constraint of the machine instruction used to ----
169 /// create this SIMemOpInfo. ----
170 AtomicOrdering getFailureOrdering() const { 0
171 return FailureOrdering; 0
172 } ----
173 ----
174 /// \returns The address spaces be accessed by the machine ----
175 /// instruction used to create this SIMemOpInfo. ----
176 SIAtomicAddrSpace getInstrAddrSpace() const { 0
177 return InstrAddrSpace; 0
178 } ----
179 ----
180 /// \returns The address spaces that must be ordered by the machine ----
181 /// instruction used to create this SIMemOpInfo. ----
182 SIAtomicAddrSpace getOrderingAddrSpace() const { 0
183 return OrderingAddrSpace; 0
184 } ----
185 ----
186 /// \returns Return true iff memory ordering of operations on ----
187 /// different address spaces is required. ----

191 ----
192 /// \returns True if memory access of the machine instruction used to ----

636 void SIMemOpAccess::reportUnsupported(const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
637 const char *Msg) const { ----
638 const Function &Func = MI->getParent()->getParent()->getFunction(); 0
639 DiagnosticInfoUnsupported Diag(Func, Msg, MI->getDebugLoc()); 0
640 Func.getContext().diagnose(Diag); 0
641 } 0
642 ----
643 std::optional> ----
644 SIMemOpAccess::toSIAtomicScope(SyncScope::ID SSID, 0
645 SIAtomicAddrSpace InstrAddrSpace) const { ----
646 if (SSID == SyncScope::System) 0
647 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM, SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC, true); 0
648 if (SSID == MMI->getAgentSSID()) 0
649 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::AGENT, SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC, true); 0
650 if (SSID == MMI->getWorkgroupSSID()) 0
651 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP, SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC, 0
652 true); 0
653 if (SSID == MMI->getWavefrontSSID()) 0
654 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT, SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC, 0
655 true); 0
656 if (SSID == SyncScope::SingleThread) 0
657 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD, SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC, 0
658 true); 0
659 if (SSID == MMI->getSystemOneAddressSpaceSSID()) 0
660 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM, 0
661 SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC & InstrAddrSpace, false); 0
662 if (SSID == MMI->getAgentOneAddressSpaceSSID()) 0
663 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::AGENT, 0
664 SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC & InstrAddrSpace, false); 0
665 if (SSID == MMI->getWorkgroupOneAddressSpaceSSID()) 0
666 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP, 0
667 SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC & InstrAddrSpace, false); 0
668 if (SSID == MMI->getWavefrontOneAddressSpaceSSID()) 0
669 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT, 0
670 SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC & InstrAddrSpace, false); 0
671 if (SSID == MMI->getSingleThreadOneAddressSpaceSSID()) 0
672 return std::tuple(SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD, 0
673 SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC & InstrAddrSpace, false); 0
674 return std::nullopt; 0
675 } ----
676 ----
677 SIAtomicAddrSpace SIMemOpAccess::toSIAtomicAddrSpace(unsigned AS) const { 0
678 if (AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS) 0
679 return SIAtomicAddrSpace::FLAT; 0
680 if (AS == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS) 0
681 return SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL; 0
682 if (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS) 0
683 return SIAtomicAddrSpace::LDS; 0
684 if (AS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS) 0
685 return SIAtomicAddrSpace::SCRATCH; 0
686 if (AS == AMDGPUAS::REGION_ADDRESS) 0
687 return SIAtomicAddrSpace::GDS; 0
688 ----
689 return SIAtomicAddrSpace::OTHER; 0
690 } ----
691 ----
692 SIMemOpAccess::SIMemOpAccess(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
693 MMI = &MF.getMMI().getObjFileInfo(); 0
694 } 0
695 ----
696 std::optional SIMemOpAccess::constructFromMIWithMMO( 0
697 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI) const { ----
698 assert(MI->getNumMemOperands() > 0); 0
699 ----
700 SyncScope::ID SSID = SyncScope::SingleThread; 0
701 AtomicOrdering Ordering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic; 0
702 AtomicOrdering FailureOrdering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic; 0
703 SIAtomicAddrSpace InstrAddrSpace = SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE; 0
704 bool IsNonTemporal = true; 0
705 bool IsVolatile = false; 0
706 ----
707 // Validator should check whether or not MMOs cover the entire set of ----
708 // locations accessed by the memory instruction. ----
709 for (const auto &MMO : MI->memoperands()) { 0
710 IsNonTemporal &= MMO->isNonTemporal(); 0
711 IsVolatile |= MMO->isVolatile(); 0
712 InstrAddrSpace |= ----
713 toSIAtomicAddrSpace(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace()); 0
714 AtomicOrdering OpOrdering = MMO->getSuccessOrdering(); 0
715 if (OpOrdering != AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic) { 0
716 const auto &IsSyncScopeInclusion = ----
717 MMI->isSyncScopeInclusion(SSID, MMO->getSyncScopeID()); 0
718 if (!IsSyncScopeInclusion) { 0
719 reportUnsupported(MI, 0
720 "Unsupported non-inclusive atomic synchronization scope"); ----
721 return std::nullopt; 0
722 } ----
723 ----
724 SSID = *IsSyncScopeInclusion ? SSID : MMO->getSyncScopeID(); 0
725 Ordering = getMergedAtomicOrdering(Ordering, OpOrdering); 0
726 assert(MMO->getFailureOrdering() != AtomicOrdering::Release && 0
727 MMO->getFailureOrdering() != AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease); ----
728 FailureOrdering = ----
729 getMergedAtomicOrdering(FailureOrdering, MMO->getFailureOrdering()); 0
730 } ----
731 } ----
732 ----
733 SIAtomicScope Scope = SIAtomicScope::NONE; 0
734 SIAtomicAddrSpace OrderingAddrSpace = SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE; 0
735 bool IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering = false; 0
736 if (Ordering != AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic) { 0
737 auto ScopeOrNone = toSIAtomicScope(SSID, InstrAddrSpace); 0
738 if (!ScopeOrNone) { 0
739 reportUnsupported(MI, "Unsupported atomic synchronization scope"); 0
740 return std::nullopt; 0
741 } ----
742 std::tie(Scope, OrderingAddrSpace, IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering) = 0
743 *ScopeOrNone; 0
744 if ((OrderingAddrSpace == SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) || 0
745 ((OrderingAddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC) != OrderingAddrSpace) || 0
746 ((InstrAddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC) == SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE)) { 0
747 reportUnsupported(MI, "Unsupported atomic address space"); 0
748 return std::nullopt; 0
749 } ----
750 } ----
751 return SIMemOpInfo(Ordering, Scope, OrderingAddrSpace, InstrAddrSpace, 0
752 IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering, FailureOrdering, IsVolatile, ----
753 IsNonTemporal); 0
754 } ----
755 ----
756 std::optional ----
757 SIMemOpAccess::getLoadInfo(const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI) const { 0
758 assert(MI->getDesc().TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::maybeAtomic); 0
759 ----
760 if (!(MI->mayLoad() && !MI->mayStore())) 0
761 return std::nullopt; 0
762 ----
763 // Be conservative if there are no memory operands. ----
764 if (MI->getNumMemOperands() == 0) 0
765 return SIMemOpInfo(); 0
766 ----
767 return constructFromMIWithMMO(MI); 0
768 } ----
769 ----
770 std::optional ----
771 SIMemOpAccess::getStoreInfo(const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI) const { 0
772 assert(MI->getDesc().TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::maybeAtomic); 0
773 ----
774 if (!(!MI->mayLoad() && MI->mayStore())) 0
775 return std::nullopt; 0
776 ----
777 // Be conservative if there are no memory operands. ----
778 if (MI->getNumMemOperands() == 0) 0
779 return SIMemOpInfo(); 0
780 ----
781 return constructFromMIWithMMO(MI); 0
782 } ----
783 ----
784 std::optional ----
785 SIMemOpAccess::getAtomicFenceInfo(const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI) const { 0
786 assert(MI->getDesc().TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::maybeAtomic); 0
787 ----
788 if (MI->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::ATOMIC_FENCE) 0
789 return std::nullopt; 0
790 ----
791 AtomicOrdering Ordering = ----
792 static_cast(MI->getOperand(0).getImm()); 0
793 ----
794 SyncScope::ID SSID = static_cast(MI->getOperand(1).getImm()); 0
795 auto ScopeOrNone = toSIAtomicScope(SSID, SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC); 0
796 if (!ScopeOrNone) { 0
797 reportUnsupported(MI, "Unsupported atomic synchronization scope"); 0
798 return std::nullopt; 0
799 } ----
800 ----
801 SIAtomicScope Scope = SIAtomicScope::NONE; 0
802 SIAtomicAddrSpace OrderingAddrSpace = SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE; 0
803 bool IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering = false; 0
804 std::tie(Scope, OrderingAddrSpace, IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering) = 0
805 *ScopeOrNone; 0
806 ----
807 if ((OrderingAddrSpace == SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) || 0
808 ((OrderingAddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC) != OrderingAddrSpace)) { 0
809 reportUnsupported(MI, "Unsupported atomic address space"); 0
810 return std::nullopt; 0
811 } ----
812 ----
813 return SIMemOpInfo(Ordering, Scope, OrderingAddrSpace, SIAtomicAddrSpace::ATOMIC, 0
814 IsCrossAddressSpaceOrdering, AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic); 0
815 } ----

825 if (MI->getNumMemOperands() == 0) 0

838 AMDGPU::CPol::CPol Bit) const { ----

840 if (!CPol) 0

847 /* static */ ----
848 std::unique_ptr SICacheControl::create(const GCNSubtarget &ST) { 0
849 GCNSubtarget::Generation Generation = ST.getGeneration(); 0
850 if (ST.hasGFX940Insts()) 0
851 return std::make_unique(ST); 0
852 if (ST.hasGFX90AInsts()) 0
853 return std::make_unique(ST); 0
854 if (Generation <= AMDGPUSubtarget::SOUTHERN_ISLANDS) 0
855 return std::make_unique(ST); 0
856 if (Generation < AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10) 0
857 return std::make_unique(ST); 0
858 if (Generation < AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX11) 0
859 return std::make_unique(ST); 0
860 return std::make_unique(ST); 0

862 ----
863 bool SIGfx6CacheControl::enableLoadCacheBypass( 0
864 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, ----
865 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
866 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
867 assert(MI->mayLoad() && !MI->mayStore()); 0
868 bool Changed = false; 0
869 ----
870 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
871 switch (Scope) { 0
872 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
873 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
874 // Set L1 cache policy to MISS_EVICT. ----
875 // Note: there is no L2 cache bypass policy at the ISA level. ----
876 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
877 break; 0
878 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
879 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
880 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
881 // No cache to bypass. ----
882 break; 0
883 default: 0
884 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
885 } ----
886 } ----
887 ----
888 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory caches ----
889 /// to be bypassed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
890 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
891 /// memory. ----
892 ----
893 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
894 ----
895 return Changed; 0
896 } ----
897 ----
898 bool SIGfx6CacheControl::enableStoreCacheBypass( 0
899 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, ----
900 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
901 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
902 assert(!MI->mayLoad() && MI->mayStore()); 0
903 bool Changed = false; 0
904 ----
905 /// The L1 cache is write through so does not need to be bypassed. There is no ----
906 /// bypass control for the L2 cache at the isa level. ----
907 ----
908 return Changed; 0
909 } ----
910 ----
911 bool SIGfx6CacheControl::enableRMWCacheBypass( 0
912 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, ----
913 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
914 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
915 assert(MI->mayLoad() && MI->mayStore()); 0
916 bool Changed = false; 0
917 ----
918 /// Do not set GLC for RMW atomic operations as L0/L1 cache is automatically ----
919 /// bypassed, and the GLC bit is instead used to indicate if they are ----
920 /// return or no-return. ----
921 /// Note: there is no L2 cache coherent bypass control at the ISA level. ----
922 ----
923 return Changed; 0
924 } ----
925 ----
926 bool SIGfx6CacheControl::enableVolatileAndOrNonTemporal( 0
927 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, SIMemOp Op, ----
928 bool IsVolatile, bool IsNonTemporal) const { ----
929 // Only handle load and store, not atomic read-modify-write insructions. The ----
930 // latter use glc to indicate if the atomic returns a result and so must not ----
931 // be used for cache control. ----
932 assert(MI->mayLoad() ^ MI->mayStore()); 0
933 ----
934 // Only update load and store, not LLVM IR atomic read-modify-write ----
935 // instructions. The latter are always marked as volatile so cannot sensibly ----
936 // handle it as do not want to pessimize all atomics. Also they do not support ----
937 // the nontemporal attribute. ----
938 assert(Op == SIMemOp::LOAD || Op == SIMemOp::STORE); 0
939 ----
940 bool Changed = false; 0
941 ----
942 if (IsVolatile) { 0
943 // Set L1 cache policy to be MISS_EVICT for load instructions ----
944 // and MISS_LRU for store instructions. ----
945 // Note: there is no L2 cache bypass policy at the ISA level. ----
946 if (Op == SIMemOp::LOAD) 0
947 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
948 ----
949 // Ensure operation has completed at system scope to cause all volatile ----
950 // operations to be visible outside the program in a global order. Do not ----
951 // request cross address space as only the global address space can be ----
952 // observable outside the program, so no need to cause a waitcnt for LDS ----
953 // address space operations. ----
954 Changed |= insertWait(MI, SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM, AddrSpace, Op, false, 0
955 Position::AFTER); ----
956 ----
957 return Changed; 0
958 } ----
959 ----
960 if (IsNonTemporal) { 0
961 // Setting both GLC and SLC configures L1 cache policy to MISS_EVICT ----
962 // for both loads and stores, and the L2 cache policy to STREAM. ----
963 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
964 Changed |= enableSLCBit(MI); 0
965 return Changed; 0
966 } ----
967 ----
968 return Changed; 0
969 } ----
970 ----
971 bool SIGfx6CacheControl::insertWait(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
972 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
973 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
974 SIMemOp Op, ----
975 bool IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, ----
976 Position Pos) const { ----
977 bool Changed = false; 0
978 ----
979 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
980 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
981 ----
982 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
983 ++MI; 0
984 ----
985 bool VMCnt = false; 0
986 bool LGKMCnt = false; 0
987 ----
988 if ((AddrSpace & (SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL | SIAtomicAddrSpace::SCRATCH)) != 0
989 SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { ----
990 switch (Scope) { 0
991 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
992 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
993 VMCnt |= true; 0
994 break; 0
995 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
996 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
997 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
998 // The L1 cache keeps all memory operations in order for ----
999 // wavefronts in the same work-group. ----
1000 break; 0
1001 default: 0
1002 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1003 } ----
1004 } ----
1005 ----
1006 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::LDS) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1007 switch (Scope) { 0
1008 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1009 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1010 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: ----
1011 // If no cross address space ordering then an "S_WAITCNT lgkmcnt(0)" is ----
1012 // not needed as LDS operations for all waves are executed in a total ----
1013 // global ordering as observed by all waves. Required if also ----
1014 // synchronizing with global/GDS memory as LDS operations could be ----
1015 // reordered with respect to later global/GDS memory operations of the ----
1016 // same wave. ----
1017 LGKMCnt |= IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering; 0
1018 break; 0
1019 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: 0
1020 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1021 // The LDS keeps all memory operations in order for ----
1022 // the same wavefront. ----
1023 break; 0
1024 default: 0
1025 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1026 } ----
1027 } ----
1028 ----
1029 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GDS) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1030 switch (Scope) { 0
1031 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1032 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1033 // If no cross address space ordering then an GDS "S_WAITCNT lgkmcnt(0)" ----
1034 // is not needed as GDS operations for all waves are executed in a total ----
1035 // global ordering as observed by all waves. Required if also ----
1036 // synchronizing with global/LDS memory as GDS operations could be ----
1037 // reordered with respect to later global/LDS memory operations of the ----
1038 // same wave. ----
1039 LGKMCnt |= IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering; 0
1040 break; 0
1041 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1042 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
1043 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1044 // The GDS keeps all memory operations in order for ----
1045 // the same work-group. ----
1046 break; 0
1047 default: 0
1048 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1049 } ----
1050 } ----
1051 ----
1052 if (VMCnt || LGKMCnt) { 0
1053 unsigned WaitCntImmediate = ----
1054 AMDGPU::encodeWaitcnt(IV, 0
1055 VMCnt ? 0 : getVmcntBitMask(IV), 0
1056 getExpcntBitMask(IV), 0
1057 LGKMCnt ? 0 : getLgkmcntBitMask(IV)); 0
1058 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT)).addImm(WaitCntImmediate); 0
1059 Changed = true; 0
1060 } ----
1061 ----
1062 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1063 --MI; 0
1064 ----
1065 return Changed; 0
1066 } 0
1067 ----
1068 bool SIGfx6CacheControl::insertAcquire(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
1069 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1070 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
1071 Position Pos) const { ----
1072 if (!InsertCacheInv) 0
1073 return false; 0
1074 ----
1075 bool Changed = false; 0
1076 ----
1077 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1078 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1079 ----
1080 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1081 ++MI; 0
1082 ----
1083 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1084 switch (Scope) { 0
1085 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1086 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1087 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_WBINVL1)); 0
1088 Changed = true; 0
1089 break; 0
1090 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1091 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
1092 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1093 // No cache to invalidate. ----
1094 break; 0
1095 default: 0
1096 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1097 } ----
1098 } ----
1099 ----
1100 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory cache ----
1101 /// to be flushed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1102 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1103 /// memory. ----
1104 ----
1105 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
1106 ----
1107 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1108 --MI; 0
1109 ----
1110 return Changed; 0
1111 } 0
1112 ----
1113 bool SIGfx6CacheControl::insertRelease(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
1114 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1115 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
1116 bool IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, ----
1117 Position Pos) const { ----
1118 return insertWait(MI, Scope, AddrSpace, SIMemOp::LOAD | SIMemOp::STORE, 0
1119 IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, Pos); 0
1120 } ----
1121 ----
1122 bool SIGfx7CacheControl::insertAcquire(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0

1124 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----

1126 if (!InsertCacheInv) 0
1127 return false; 0
1128 ----
1129 bool Changed = false; 0
1130 ----
1131 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1132 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1133 ----
1134 const GCNSubtarget &STM = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
1135 ----
1136 const unsigned InvalidateL1 = STM.isAmdPalOS() || STM.isMesa3DOS() 0
1137 ? AMDGPU::BUFFER_WBINVL1 0
1138 : AMDGPU::BUFFER_WBINVL1_VOL; 0
1139 ----
1140 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1141 ++MI; 0
1142 ----
1143 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1144 switch (Scope) { 0
1145 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1146 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1147 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(InvalidateL1)); 0
1148 Changed = true; 0
1149 break; 0
1150 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1151 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
1152 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1153 // No cache to invalidate. ----
1154 break; 0
1155 default: 0
1156 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1157 } ----
1158 } ----
1159 ----
1160 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory cache ----
1161 /// to be flushed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1162 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1163 /// memory. ----
1164 ----
1165 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----

1171 } 0
1172 ----
1173 bool SIGfx90ACacheControl::enableLoadCacheBypass( 0
1174 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, ----
1175 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1176 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
1177 assert(MI->mayLoad() && !MI->mayStore()); 0
1178 bool Changed = false; 0
1179 ----
1180 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1181 switch (Scope) { 0
1182 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1183 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1184 // Set the L1 cache policy to MISS_LRU. ----
1185 // Note: there is no L2 cache bypass policy at the ISA level. ----
1186 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
1187 break; 0
1188 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1189 // In threadgroup split mode the waves of a work-group can be executing on ----
1190 // different CUs. Therefore need to bypass the L1 which is per CU. ----
1191 // Otherwise in non-threadgroup split mode all waves of a work-group are ----
1192 // on the same CU, and so the L1 does not need to be bypassed. ----
1193 if (ST.isTgSplitEnabled()) 0
1194 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
1195 break; 0
1196 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: 0
1197 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1198 // No cache to bypass. ----
1199 break; 0
1200 default: 0
1201 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1202 } ----
1203 } ----
1204 ----
1205 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory caches ----
1206 /// to be bypassed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1207 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1208 /// memory. ----
1209 ----
1210 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
1211 ----
1212 return Changed; 0
1213 } ----
1214 ----
1215 bool SIGfx90ACacheControl::enableStoreCacheBypass( 0
1216 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, ----
1217 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1218 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
1219 assert(!MI->mayLoad() && MI->mayStore()); 0
1220 bool Changed = false; 0
1221 ----
1222 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1223 switch (Scope) { 0
1224 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1225 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1226 /// Do not set glc for store atomic operations as they implicitly write ----
1227 /// through the L1 cache. ----
1228 break; 0
1229 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1230 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
1231 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1232 // No cache to bypass. Store atomics implicitly write through the L1 ----
1233 // cache. ----
1234 break; 0
1235 default: 0
1236 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1237 } ----
1238 } ----
1239 ----
1240 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory caches ----
1241 /// to be bypassed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1242 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1243 /// memory. ----
1244 ----
1245 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
1246 ----
1247 return Changed; 0
1248 } ----
1249 ----
1250 bool SIGfx90ACacheControl::enableRMWCacheBypass( 0
1251 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, ----
1252 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1253 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
1254 assert(MI->mayLoad() && MI->mayStore()); 0
1255 bool Changed = false; 0
1256 ----
1257 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1258 switch (Scope) { 0
1259 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1260 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1261 /// Do not set glc for RMW atomic operations as they implicitly bypass ----
1262 /// the L1 cache, and the glc bit is instead used to indicate if they are ----
1263 /// return or no-return. ----
1264 break; 0
1265 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1266 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
1267 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1268 // No cache to bypass. RMW atomics implicitly bypass the L1 cache. ----
1269 break; 0
1270 default: 0
1271 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1272 } ----
1273 } ----
1274 ----
1275 return Changed; 0
1276 } ----
1277 ----
1278 bool SIGfx90ACacheControl::enableVolatileAndOrNonTemporal( 0
1279 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, SIMemOp Op, ----
1280 bool IsVolatile, bool IsNonTemporal) const { ----
1281 // Only handle load and store, not atomic read-modify-write insructions. The ----
1282 // latter use glc to indicate if the atomic returns a result and so must not ----
1283 // be used for cache control. ----
1284 assert(MI->mayLoad() ^ MI->mayStore()); 0
1285 ----
1286 // Only update load and store, not LLVM IR atomic read-modify-write ----
1287 // instructions. The latter are always marked as volatile so cannot sensibly ----
1288 // handle it as do not want to pessimize all atomics. Also they do not support ----
1289 // the nontemporal attribute. ----
1290 assert(Op == SIMemOp::LOAD || Op == SIMemOp::STORE); 0
1291 ----
1292 bool Changed = false; 0
1293 ----
1294 if (IsVolatile) { 0
1295 // Set L1 cache policy to be MISS_EVICT for load instructions ----
1296 // and MISS_LRU for store instructions. ----
1297 // Note: there is no L2 cache bypass policy at the ISA level. ----
1298 if (Op == SIMemOp::LOAD) 0
1299 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
1300 ----
1301 // Ensure operation has completed at system scope to cause all volatile ----
1302 // operations to be visible outside the program in a global order. Do not ----
1303 // request cross address space as only the global address space can be ----
1304 // observable outside the program, so no need to cause a waitcnt for LDS ----
1305 // address space operations. ----
1306 Changed |= insertWait(MI, SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM, AddrSpace, Op, false, 0
1307 Position::AFTER); ----
1308 ----
1309 return Changed; 0
1310 } ----
1311 ----
1312 if (IsNonTemporal) { 0
1313 // Setting both GLC and SLC configures L1 cache policy to MISS_EVICT ----
1314 // for both loads and stores, and the L2 cache policy to STREAM. ----
1315 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
1316 Changed |= enableSLCBit(MI); 0
1317 return Changed; 0
1318 } ----
1319 ----
1320 return Changed; 0
1321 } ----
1322 ----
1323 bool SIGfx90ACacheControl::insertWait(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
1324 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1325 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
1326 SIMemOp Op, ----
1327 bool IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, ----
1328 Position Pos) const { ----
1329 if (ST.isTgSplitEnabled()) { 0
1330 // In threadgroup split mode the waves of a work-group can be executing on ----
1331 // different CUs. Therefore need to wait for global or GDS memory operations ----
1332 // to complete to ensure they are visible to waves in the other CUs. ----
1333 // Otherwise in non-threadgroup split mode all waves of a work-group are on ----
1334 // the same CU, so no need to wait for global memory as all waves in the ----
1335 // work-group access the same the L1, nor wait for GDS as access are ordered ----
1336 // on a CU. ----
1337 if (((AddrSpace & (SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL | SIAtomicAddrSpace::SCRATCH | 0
1338 SIAtomicAddrSpace::GDS)) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) && 0
1339 (Scope == SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP)) { ----
1340 // Same as GFX7 using agent scope. ----
1341 Scope = SIAtomicScope::AGENT; 0
1342 } ----
1343 // In threadgroup split mode LDS cannot be allocated so no need to wait for ----
1344 // LDS memory operations. ----
1345 AddrSpace &= ~SIAtomicAddrSpace::LDS; 0
1346 } ----
1347 return SIGfx7CacheControl::insertWait(MI, Scope, AddrSpace, Op, 0
1348 IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, Pos); 0
1349 } ----
1350 ----
1351 bool SIGfx90ACacheControl::insertAcquire(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
1352 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1353 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
1354 Position Pos) const { ----
1355 if (!InsertCacheInv) 0
1356 return false; 0
1357 ----
1358 bool Changed = false; 0
1359 ----
1360 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1361 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1362 ----
1363 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1364 ++MI; 0
1365 ----
1366 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1367 switch (Scope) { 0
1368 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1369 // Ensures that following loads will not see stale remote VMEM data or ----
1370 // stale local VMEM data with MTYPE NC. Local VMEM data with MTYPE RW and ----
1371 // CC will never be stale due to the local memory probes. ----
1372 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_INVL2)); 0
1373 // Inserting a "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" after is not required because the ----
1374 // hardware does not reorder memory operations by the same wave with ----
1375 // respect to a preceding "BUFFER_INVL2". The invalidate is guaranteed to ----
1376 // remove any cache lines of earlier writes by the same wave and ensures ----
1377 // later reads by the same wave will refetch the cache lines. ----
1378 Changed = true; 0
1379 break; 0
1380 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: 0
1381 // Same as GFX7. ----
1382 break; 0
1383 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1384 // In threadgroup split mode the waves of a work-group can be executing on ----
1385 // different CUs. Therefore need to invalidate the L1 which is per CU. ----
1386 // Otherwise in non-threadgroup split mode all waves of a work-group are ----
1387 // on the same CU, and so the L1 does not need to be invalidated. ----
1388 if (ST.isTgSplitEnabled()) { 0
1389 // Same as GFX7 using agent scope. ----
1390 Scope = SIAtomicScope::AGENT; 0
1391 } ----
1392 break; 0
1393 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: 0
1394 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1395 // Same as GFX7. ----
1396 break; 0
1397 default: 0
1398 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1399 } ----
1400 } ----
1401 ----
1402 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory cache ----
1403 /// to be flushed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1404 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1405 /// memory. ----
1406 ----
1407 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
1408 ----
1409 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1410 --MI; 0
1411 ----
1412 Changed |= SIGfx7CacheControl::insertAcquire(MI, Scope, AddrSpace, Pos); 0
1413 ----
1414 return Changed; 0
1415 } 0
1416 ----
1417 bool SIGfx90ACacheControl::insertRelease(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
1418 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1419 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
1420 bool IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, ----
1421 Position Pos) const { ----
1422 bool Changed = false; 0
1423 ----
1424 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1425 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1426 ----
1427 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1428 ++MI; 0
1429 ----
1430 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1431 switch (Scope) { 0
1432 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1433 // Inserting a "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" before is not required because the ----
1434 // hardware does not reorder memory operations by the same wave with ----
1435 // respect to a following "BUFFER_WBL2". The "BUFFER_WBL2" is guaranteed ----
1436 // to initiate writeback of any dirty cache lines of earlier writes by the ----
1437 // same wave. A "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" is needed after to ensure the ----
1438 // writeback has completed. ----
1439 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_WBL2)) 0
1440 // Set SC bits to indicate system scope. ----
1441 .addImm(AMDGPU::CPol::SC0 | AMDGPU::CPol::SC1); 0
1442 // Followed by same as GFX7, which will ensure the necessary "S_WAITCNT ----
1443 // vmcnt(0)" needed by the "BUFFER_WBL2". ----
1444 Changed = true; 0
1445 break; 0
1446 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: 0
1447 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: ----
1448 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
1449 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1450 // Same as GFX7. ----
1451 break; 0
1452 default: 0
1453 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1454 } ----
1455 } ----
1456 ----
1457 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1458 --MI; 0
1459 ----
1460 Changed |= 0
1461 SIGfx7CacheControl::insertRelease(MI, Scope, AddrSpace, 0
1462 IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, Pos); ----
1463 ----
1464 return Changed; 0
1465 } 0

1467 bool SIGfx940CacheControl::enableLoadCacheBypass( 0
1468 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1469 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
1470 assert(MI->mayLoad() && !MI->mayStore()); 0
1471 bool Changed = false; 0
1472 ----
1473 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1474 switch (Scope) { 0
1475 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1476 // Set SC bits to indicate system scope. ----
1477 Changed |= enableSC0Bit(MI); 0
1478 Changed |= enableSC1Bit(MI); 0
1479 break; 0
1480 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: 0
1481 // Set SC bits to indicate agent scope. ----
1482 Changed |= enableSC1Bit(MI); 0
1483 break; 0
1484 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1485 // In threadgroup split mode the waves of a work-group can be executing on ----
1486 // different CUs. Therefore need to bypass the L1 which is per CU. ----
1487 // Otherwise in non-threadgroup split mode all waves of a work-group are ----
1488 // on the same CU, and so the L1 does not need to be bypassed. Setting SC ----
1489 // bits to indicate work-group scope will do this automatically. ----
1490 Changed |= enableSC0Bit(MI); 0
1491 break; 0
1492 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: 0
1493 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1494 // Leave SC bits unset to indicate wavefront scope. ----
1495 break; 0
1496 default: 0
1497 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1498 } ----
1499 } ----

1501 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory caches ----
1502 /// to be bypassed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1503 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1504 /// memory. ----
1505 ----
1506 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
1507 ----
1508 return Changed; 0
1509 } ----

1530 Changed |= enableSC0Bit(MI); 0

1551 bool SIGfx940CacheControl::enableRMWCacheBypass( 0

1554 assert(MI->mayLoad() && MI->mayStore()); 0

1620 bool SIGfx940CacheControl::insertAcquire(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
1621 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1622 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
1623 Position Pos) const { ----
1624 if (!InsertCacheInv) 0
1625 return false; 0
1626 ----
1627 bool Changed = false; 0
1628 ----
1629 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1630 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1631 ----
1632 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1633 ++MI; 0
1634 ----
1635 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1636 switch (Scope) { 0
1637 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1638 // Ensures that following loads will not see stale remote VMEM data or ----
1639 // stale local VMEM data with MTYPE NC. Local VMEM data with MTYPE RW and ----
1640 // CC will never be stale due to the local memory probes. ----
1641 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_INV)) 0
1642 // Set SC bits to indicate system scope. ----
1643 .addImm(AMDGPU::CPol::SC0 | AMDGPU::CPol::SC1); 0
1644 // Inserting a "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" after is not required because the ----
1645 // hardware does not reorder memory operations by the same wave with ----
1646 // respect to a preceding "BUFFER_INV". The invalidate is guaranteed to ----
1647 // remove any cache lines of earlier writes by the same wave and ensures ----
1648 // later reads by the same wave will refetch the cache lines. ----
1649 Changed = true; 0
1650 break; 0
1651 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: 0
1652 // Ensures that following loads will not see stale remote date or local ----
1653 // MTYPE NC global data. Local MTYPE RW and CC memory will never be stale ----
1654 // due to the memory probes. ----
1655 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_INV)) 0
1656 // Set SC bits to indicate agent scope. ----
1657 .addImm(AMDGPU::CPol::SC1); 0
1658 // Inserting "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" is not required because the hardware ----
1659 // does not reorder memory operations with respect to preceeding buffer ----
1660 // invalidate. The invalidate is guaranteed to remove any cache lines of ----
1661 // earlier writes and ensures later writes will refetch the cache lines. ----
1662 Changed = true; 0
1663 break; 0
1664 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1665 // In threadgroup split mode the waves of a work-group can be executing on ----
1666 // different CUs. Therefore need to invalidate the L1 which is per CU. ----
1667 // Otherwise in non-threadgroup split mode all waves of a work-group are ----
1668 // on the same CU, and so the L1 does not need to be invalidated. ----
1669 if (ST.isTgSplitEnabled()) { 0
1670 // Ensures L1 is invalidated if in threadgroup split mode. In ----
1671 // non-threadgroup split mode it is a NOP, but no point generating it in ----
1672 // that case if know not in that mode. ----
1673 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_INV)) 0
1674 // Set SC bits to indicate work-group scope. ----
1675 .addImm(AMDGPU::CPol::SC0); 0
1676 // Inserting "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" is not required because the hardware ----
1677 // does not reorder memory operations with respect to preceeding buffer ----
1678 // invalidate. The invalidate is guaranteed to remove any cache lines of ----
1679 // earlier writes and ensures later writes will refetch the cache lines. ----
1680 Changed = true; 0
1681 } ----
1682 break; 0
1683 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: 0
1684 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1685 // Could generate "BUFFER_INV" but it would do nothing as there are no ----
1686 // caches to invalidate. ----
1687 break; 0
1688 default: 0
1689 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1690 } ----
1691 } ----
1692 ----
1693 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory cache ----
1694 /// to be flushed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1695 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1696 /// memory. ----
1697 ----
1698 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
1699 ----
1700 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1701 --MI; 0
1702 ----
1703 return Changed; 0
1704 } 0
1705 ----
1706 bool SIGfx940CacheControl::insertRelease(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0
1707 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1708 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, ----
1709 bool IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, ----
1710 Position Pos) const { ----
1711 bool Changed = false; 0
1712 ----
1713 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1714 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1715 ----
1716 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1717 ++MI; 0
1718 ----
1719 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1720 switch (Scope) { 0
1721 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1722 // Inserting a "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" before is not required because the ----
1723 // hardware does not reorder memory operations by the same wave with ----
1724 // respect to a following "BUFFER_WBL2". The "BUFFER_WBL2" is guaranteed ----
1725 // to initiate writeback of any dirty cache lines of earlier writes by the ----
1726 // same wave. A "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" is needed after to ensure the ----
1727 // writeback has completed. ----
1728 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_WBL2)) 0
1729 // Set SC bits to indicate system scope. ----
1730 .addImm(AMDGPU::CPol::SC0 | AMDGPU::CPol::SC1); 0
1731 // Since AddrSpace contains SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL and Scope is ----
1732 // SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM, the following insertWait will generate the ----
1733 // required "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)" needed by the "BUFFER_WBL2". ----
1734 Changed = true; 0
1735 break; 0
1736 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: 0
1737 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::BUFFER_WBL2)) 0
1738 // Set SC bits to indicate agent scope. ----
1739 .addImm(AMDGPU::CPol::SC1); 0
1740 ----
1741 // Since AddrSpace contains SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL and Scope is ----
1742 // SIAtomicScope::AGENT, the following insertWait will generate the ----
1743 // required "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)". ----
1744 Changed = true; 0
1745 break; 0
1746 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1747 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: ----
1748 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1749 // Do not generate "BUFFER_WBL2" as there are no caches it would ----
1750 // writeback, and would require an otherwise unnecessary ----
1751 // "S_WAITCNT vmcnt(0)". ----
1752 break; 0
1753 default: 0
1754 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1755 } ----
1756 } ----
1757 ----
1758 if (Pos == Position::AFTER) 0
1759 --MI; 0
1760 ----
1761 // Ensure the necessary S_WAITCNT needed by any "BUFFER_WBL2" as well as other ----
1762 // S_WAITCNT needed. ----
1763 Changed |= insertWait(MI, Scope, AddrSpace, SIMemOp::LOAD | SIMemOp::STORE, 0
1764 IsCrossAddrSpaceOrdering, Pos); ----
1765 ----
1766 return Changed; 0
1767 } 0

1769 bool SIGfx10CacheControl::enableLoadCacheBypass( 0
1770 const MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, ----
1771 SIAtomicScope Scope, ----
1772 SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace) const { ----
1773 assert(MI->mayLoad() && !MI->mayStore()); 0
1774 bool Changed = false; 0
1775 ----
1776 if ((AddrSpace & SIAtomicAddrSpace::GLOBAL) != SIAtomicAddrSpace::NONE) { 0
1777 switch (Scope) { 0
1778 case SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM: 0
1779 case SIAtomicScope::AGENT: ----
1780 // Set the L0 and L1 cache policies to MISS_EVICT. ----
1781 // Note: there is no L2 cache coherent bypass control at the ISA level. ----
1782 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
1783 Changed |= enableDLCBit(MI); 0
1784 break; 0
1785 case SIAtomicScope::WORKGROUP: 0
1786 // In WGP mode the waves of a work-group can be executing on either CU of ----
1787 // the WGP. Therefore need to bypass the L0 which is per CU. Otherwise in ----
1788 // CU mode all waves of a work-group are on the same CU, and so the L0 ----
1789 // does not need to be bypassed. ----
1790 if (!ST.isCuModeEnabled()) 0
1791 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
1792 break; 0
1793 case SIAtomicScope::WAVEFRONT: 0
1794 case SIAtomicScope::SINGLETHREAD: ----
1795 // No cache to bypass. ----
1796 break; 0
1797 default: 0
1798 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0
1799 } ----
1800 } ----
1801 ----
1802 /// The scratch address space does not need the global memory caches ----
1803 /// to be bypassed as all memory operations by the same thread are ----
1804 /// sequentially consistent, and no other thread can access scratch ----
1805 /// memory. ----
1806 ----
1807 /// Other address spaces do not have a cache. ----
1808 ----
1809 return Changed; 0
1810 } ----

1812 bool SIGfx10CacheControl::enableVolatileAndOrNonTemporal( 0
1813 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, SIMemOp Op, ----
1814 bool IsVolatile, bool IsNonTemporal) const { ----
1815 ----
1816 // Only handle load and store, not atomic read-modify-write insructions. The ----
1817 // latter use glc to indicate if the atomic returns a result and so must not ----
1818 // be used for cache control. ----
1819 assert(MI->mayLoad() ^ MI->mayStore()); 0
1820 ----
1821 // Only update load and store, not LLVM IR atomic read-modify-write ----
1822 // instructions. The latter are always marked as volatile so cannot sensibly ----
1823 // handle it as do not want to pessimize all atomics. Also they do not support ----
1824 // the nontemporal attribute. ----
1825 assert(Op == SIMemOp::LOAD || Op == SIMemOp::STORE); 0
1826 ----
1827 bool Changed = false; 0
1828 ----
1829 if (IsVolatile) { 0
1830 // Set L0 and L1 cache policy to be MISS_EVICT for load instructions ----
1831 // and MISS_LRU for store instructions. ----
1832 // Note: there is no L2 cache coherent bypass control at the ISA level. ----
1833 if (Op == SIMemOp::LOAD) { 0
1834 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
1835 Changed |= enableDLCBit(MI); 0
1836 } ----
1837 ----
1838 // Ensure operation has completed at system scope to cause all volatile ----
1839 // operations to be visible outside the program in a global order. Do not ----
1840 // request cross address space as only the global address space can be ----
1841 // observable outside the program, so no need to cause a waitcnt for LDS ----
1842 // address space operations. ----

1863 bool SIGfx10CacheControl::insertWait(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, 0

1908 break; 0

1954 break; 0
1955 default: 0
1956 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported synchronization scope"); 0

2029 ----

2079 bool SIGfx11CacheControl::enableVolatileAndOrNonTemporal( 0
2080 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MI, SIAtomicAddrSpace AddrSpace, SIMemOp Op, ----
2081 bool IsVolatile, bool IsNonTemporal) const { ----
2082 ----
2083 // Only handle load and store, not atomic read-modify-write insructions. The ----
2084 // latter use glc to indicate if the atomic returns a result and so must not ----
2085 // be used for cache control. ----
2086 assert(MI->mayLoad() ^ MI->mayStore()); 0
2087 ----
2088 // Only update load and store, not LLVM IR atomic read-modify-write ----
2089 // instructions. The latter are always marked as volatile so cannot sensibly ----
2090 // handle it as do not want to pessimize all atomics. Also they do not support ----
2091 // the nontemporal attribute. ----
2092 assert(Op == SIMemOp::LOAD || Op == SIMemOp::STORE); 0
2093 ----
2094 bool Changed = false; 0
2095 ----
2096 if (IsVolatile) { 0
2097 // Set L0 and L1 cache policy to be MISS_EVICT for load instructions ----
2098 // and MISS_LRU for store instructions. ----
2099 // Note: there is no L2 cache coherent bypass control at the ISA level. ----
2100 if (Op == SIMemOp::LOAD) 0
2101 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
2102 ----
2103 // Set MALL NOALLOC for load and store instructions. ----
2104 Changed |= enableDLCBit(MI); 0
2105 ----
2106 // Ensure operation has completed at system scope to cause all volatile ----
2107 // operations to be visible outside the program in a global order. Do not ----
2108 // request cross address space as only the global address space can be ----
2109 // observable outside the program, so no need to cause a waitcnt for LDS ----
2110 // address space operations. ----
2111 Changed |= insertWait(MI, SIAtomicScope::SYSTEM, AddrSpace, Op, false, 0
2112 Position::AFTER); ----
2113 return Changed; 0
2114 } ----
2115 ----
2116 if (IsNonTemporal) { 0
2117 // For loads setting SLC configures L0 and L1 cache policy to HIT_EVICT ----
2118 // and L2 cache policy to STREAM. ----
2119 // For stores setting both GLC and SLC configures L0 and L1 cache policy ----
2120 // to MISS_EVICT and the L2 cache policy to STREAM. ----
2121 if (Op == SIMemOp::STORE) 0
2122 Changed |= enableGLCBit(MI); 0
2123 Changed |= enableSLCBit(MI); 0
2124 ----
2125 // Set MALL NOALLOC for load and store instructions. ----
2126 Changed |= enableDLCBit(MI); 0
2127 return Changed; 0
2128 } ----
2129 ----
2130 return Changed; 0
2131 } ----

2316 bool SIMemoryLegalizer::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
2317 bool Changed = false; 0
2318 ----
2319 SIMemOpAccess MOA(MF); 0
2320 CC = SICacheControl::create(MF.getSubtarget()); 0
2321 ----
2322 for (auto &MBB : MF) { 0
2323 for (auto MI = MBB.begin(); MI != MBB.end(); ++MI) { 0
2324 ----
2325 // Unbundle instructions after the post-RA scheduler. ----
2326 if (MI->isBundle() && MI->mayLoadOrStore()) { 0
2327 MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator II(MI->getIterator()); 0
2328 for (MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator I = ++II, E = MBB.instr_end(); 0
2329 I != E && I->isBundledWithPred(); ++I) { 0
2330 I->unbundleFromPred(); 0
2331 for (MachineOperand &MO : I->operands()) 0
2332 if (MO.isReg()) 0
2333 MO.setIsInternalRead(false); 0
2334 } ----
2335 ----
2336 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
2337 MI = II->getIterator(); 0
2338 } ----
2339 ----
2340 if (!(MI->getDesc().TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::maybeAtomic)) 0
2341 continue; 0
2342 ----
2343 if (const auto &MOI = MOA.getLoadInfo(MI)) 0
2344 Changed |= expandLoad(*MOI, MI); 0
2345 else if (const auto &MOI = MOA.getStoreInfo(MI)) { 0
2346 Changed |= expandStore(*MOI, MI); 0
2347 Changed |= CC->tryForceStoreSC0SC1(*MOI, MI); 0
2348 } else if (const auto &MOI = MOA.getAtomicFenceInfo(MI)) 0
2349 Changed |= expandAtomicFence(*MOI, MI); 0
2350 else if (const auto &MOI = MOA.getAtomicCmpxchgOrRmwInfo(MI)) 0
2351 Changed |= expandAtomicCmpxchgOrRmw(*MOI, MI); 0
2352 } ----
2353 } ----
2354 ----
2355 Changed |= removeAtomicPseudoMIs(); 0
2356 return Changed; 0
2357 } ----
